The police in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday confirmed an arrest of another suspect linked to the murders in the notorious Glebelands Hostel in Umlazi near Durban. He is expected to appear in court on Wednesday. The suspect was arrested on on Sunday following a joint operation by various police units. The police say that they followed up on information with regards to the whereabouts of wanted suspects in the Glebelands Hostel murder cases. “The members traced the man and he was searched. He was found in possession of an unlicensed 9mm pistol with 15 rounds of ammunition. He was charged for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition and he is expected to appear in the Umlazi Magistrate’s Court tomorrow,” said the police in a statement. The police added that he was linked to two murder cases at Glebelands Hostel as well as other murder cases in the Bhekithemba area. “In one of the murder cases where he was linked to, Tholakele Ngcangcatha, 30, was shot and killed at the hostel on 3 August 2017,” said Lt Col Thulani Zwane. The KZN Acting Provincial Commissioner Major General Bheki Langa welcomed the arrest and applauded the police for their work in tracing him. “Our police officers deployed in the hostel will continue with their operations in making sure that there is peace and stability at hostel,” he added. -TNA Reporter 